        about: 'Figma is the industry standard tool because it sits at the intersection of design and collaboration. Components and Auto Layout are not convenience features — they are how professional teams maintain consistency across hundreds of screens. A component is a design decision made once and applied everywhere. Change the component, and all instances update instantly.\n\nA design system is a shared language between designers and developers. Tokens are the vocabulary — named variables for colours, spacing, and typography that exist in both Figma and the codebase. Accessibility is not optional — WCAG contrast requirements, touch target sizes, and focus states apply to every design.',
